text: I have a soft spot for kevin costner. Sure he's been in some stinkers but I've never come away from one of his flicks dissing his performance. Yeah, he's over the top, but that's a good thing considering the amount of assholes I encounter in daily life who are so over the top that Kevin is low key in comparison. Whereas if brad pitt offered to buy me a drink I'd smash it in his face, if Kevin did the same I'd actually consider drinking it. So I know a little about over the top shit. And his performances and films have not deteriorated over the years. The flick with amber heard, it did zilch at the BO but I loved it, and Kevin is actually charming as the killer company man trying to patch his life and family together with duct tape before he dies. It's hard to say this, but Kevin Costner actually has a little style, and he's not a tabloid magnet and doesn't appear to whore himself in public. Who knows what goes on in the back. At least for public consumption he's a bonafide movie star. The studios have not backed his play in a while, but fuck it, he's getting paid, and at the back end of his career as a star he's still doing it up proud.

text: As this was said on Wikipedia, Criminal has received generally negative reviews from critics. On Rotten Tomatoes, the film has a rating of 31%, based on 113 reviews, with an average rating of 4.4/10. The site's consensus reads, "Despite the valiant efforts of a game and talented cast, Criminal has little to offer beyond the bare minimum expected by the most undemanding of genre enthusiasts."[30] On Metacritic, the film has a score of 37 out of 100, based on 26 critics, indicating "generally unfavorable reviews".[31] Audiences polled by CinemaScore gave the film an average grade of "B‚Äì" on an A+ to F scale.  Most people also complained that the movie is not good either because it's either the storyline or the actings.
